                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>\n                <addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>5 Inangti<add>?</add> Hackney</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                <date>29 June / 43</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I write to you<lb/> in the shape of a note be<lb/>cause I am anxious\n                to forward<lb/> you two poems by the same<lb/> post and for the same postage<lb/>\n                and as I have but little in<lb/>teresting to communicate the<lb/> apparent brevity\n                of my epistle<lb/> you will I trust kindly excuse</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I owe you an apology<lb/> for not having answered your<lb/> kind\n                favor of <date>10 January</date> long<lb/> ere this, but continued\n                indis<lb/>position since the early part<lb/> of <date>March</date> and a very\n                long<lb/> task of writing which I had<lb/> to finish as speedily as possible<lb/>\n                prevented my addressing any<lb/> of my correspondents and <add>?</add></p>\n            <p\n                rend=\"The following (page 5) is written in the opposite direction over the above text.\"/>\n            <p>where you have any money in hand for<lb/> me. Do not procure them till<add>?</add>\n                you can pay yourself<lb/> from any money you may have to transmit<lb/> to me &amp;\n                then I should be obliged by your<lb/> forwarding them by the first opportunity I\n                think<lb/> my name had better be written in them or they<lb/> will not pass without\n                a <hi rend=\"underline\">fine</hi> which I have no in<lb/>clination to pay. Papa\n                begged me to inform<lb/> you he had a small parcel for you from the <persName>Miss<lb/>\n                    <add>?</add></persName> which he will forward by the first opportunity</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Trusting this letter will find you in<lb/> health &amp; prosperity\n                    <add>?</add> in all your undertakings</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I remain dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">yours truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Grace Aguilar</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3988373d/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
