                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>2</p>\n            <p>I trust plead my excuse with<lb/> you as with others. Allow me<lb/> to thank you for\n                the 1<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi> number<lb/> of your periodical, which my<lb/> brother\n                brought me from <persName>Mr Franklin</persName><lb/> without however any message,\n                so<lb/> I do not know whether you sent<lb/> any with it and also let me<lb/> thank\n                you, for the very grati<lb/>fying notice with which you<lb/> introduce my little\n                poem “The<lb/> Chambers of the Dying” to your<lb/> readers, in your second\n                number.<lb/> I trust the poems I send may<lb/> prove suitable and acceptable<lb/>\n                the intent of both is to bring<lb/> us closer to the gracious Saviours<lb/> of\n                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>, than is often unhappily<lb/> the case with our\n                nation. They<lb/> generally place Him at a<lb/> distance. I never think of\n                deriving<lb/> comfort from the fact that He<lb/> knows &amp; loves us better\n                than<lb/> our dearest Friends on Earth, &amp; feels</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3988373d/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
