                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3988373d/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>4</p>\n            <p>to us in <placeName>England</placeName>. I do not<lb/> much understand business\n                my<lb/>self, <del>but</del> so that the slowness of<lb/> payment appears to me\n                rather<lb/> strange. You are right in sup<lb/>posing gain was not my object<lb/> in\n                publishing the work, but yet<lb/> I am not rich or even independent<lb/> enough, not\n                to feel anxious to<lb/> receive that, which if the books<lb/>\n                <del>are sold</del> or even some of them <del>have</del> are<lb/> sold at the places\n                to which they<lb/> have been sent, must be my<lb/> due an anxiety which I have<lb/>\n                no doubt you can <hi rend=\"underline\">understand</hi><lb/> but I know it is not in\n                your<lb/> power to <sic>remidy</sic> it. You will<lb/> oblige me greatly however\n                by<lb/> urging your agents to a settlement<lb/> for those they have sold. With<lb/>\n                regard to <persName>Dr Channings<add>?</add></persName> works<lb/> which you say can\n                be procured<lb/> in 5 vols for 4 Dollars—I<lb/> should like much to have them</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3988373d/canvas/p4"
                }
              ]
            }
